---
description: Avoid excessive blank lines in TypeScript files
globs: "**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Whitespace / Blank Line Rules

- Do not add blank lines between sequential statements within the same logical block (inside a try, for, if, etc.)
- One blank line is acceptable between top-level method definitions and between distinct logical sections
- Never pad the inside of control flow blocks (for, if, try) with leading/trailing blank lines

```typescript
// BAD
for (const item of items) {
   if (this.isShuttingDown) break;

   const result = await this.process(item);
   processed += result.count;

}

// GOOD
for (const item of items) {
   if (this.isShuttingDown) break;
   const result = await this.process(item);
   processed += result.count;
}
```
